# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Real-secrets file for ZeusAI / UNICORN_FINAL deployment.
#
# 1. Copy this file to `.env.secrets.local` (already gitignored).
# 2. Fill in the values below from the linked dashboards.
# 3. Run:  bash scripts/sync-secrets-to-hetzner.sh
#
# The sync script will:
#   • SSH into Hetzner (using HETZNER_KEY_PATH from .env.auto-connector)
#   • Write /root/unicorn-final/UNICORN_FINAL/.env.local with chmod 600
#   • Restart pm2 with --update-env (zero-downtime cluster reload)
#   • Verify webhook + DR autopilot armed correctly
#
# Format validation is enforced — invalid values abort the sync.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Stripe webhook secret ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Where to get it:
#   1. Stripe Dashboard → Developers → Webhooks → Add endpoint
#   2. Endpoint URL:  https://zeusai.pro/webhooks/stripe
#   3. Select events: checkout.session.completed, invoice.paid,
#                     customer.subscription.{created,updated,deleted}
#   4. Copy the "Signing secret" (starts with whsec_)
# Format: whsec_<long-base64>
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=

# ── S3 bucket for disaster-recovery backups ─────────────────────────────────
# Where to create it:
#   1. AWS Console → S3 → Create bucket
#   2. Name: zeus-dr-backups-<your-suffix>  (must be globally unique)
#   3. Region: eu-central-1 (close to Hetzner Helsinki/Falkenstein)
#   4. Block all public access: ON
#   5. Versioning: enable
#   6. Default encryption: SSE-S3 (or SSE-KMS for tighter control)
DR_S3_BUCKET=

# ── AWS IAM keys for the DR backup user ─────────────────────────────────────
# Where to get them:
#   1. AWS Console → IAM → Users → Add user
#   2. Name: zeus-dr-backup-bot
#   3. Access type: Programmatic access
#   4. Permissions: Inline policy with ONLY:
#        s3:PutObject, s3:GetObject, s3:ListBucket, s3:DeleteObject
#        on arn:aws:s3:::<DR_S3_BUCKET>/* and arn:aws:s3:::<DR_S3_BUCKET>
#   5. Copy Access Key ID (AKIA...) and Secret Access Key (40 chars)
#
# Format: AKIA + 16 chars  /  40-char base64
DR_AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=
DR_AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=

# ── DR autopilot arm flag ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Set to 1 ONLY after the three values above are real.
# The sync script will refuse to arm this if any AWS field above is empty.
DR_AUTOPILOT_ENABLED=1
